{"name": "django-percentagefield", "metadata": {"name": "django-percentagefield", "version": "0.1.6", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django :: 5.0", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Application Frameworks", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["django"], "summary": "A ``PercentageField`` for Django that shows a Decimal (ex. ``0.2100`` in the database - by default rounded to 4 decimal spaces) as a percentage in the admin (ex. ``21%``). With built-in (overridable) min and max validator to ensure a valid percentage range: 0 \u2264 x \u2264 100.", "upload_time": 1733834925}, "documentation": ["# Django Percentage Field\n\nThis package add a ``PercentageField`` to Django (also works with Unfold, some minor styling improvements needed) that\nshows a percentage in the admin as ``21%``, but stores it as a Decimal - ``0.2100`` - to the database.\nThis makes it clearer for admins what the field represents, while the decimal value makes actual calculations easier.\n\n## Installation\n\nRun `pip install django-percentagefield` (or `poetry add django-percentagefield`)\n\n## Settings\n\n- add ``django_percentagefield`` to your ``INSTALLED_APPS`` **before** ``django.contrib.admin``\n- in your ``models.py``, add the ``PercentageField`` as such:\n\n```python models.py\nfrom django.db import models\n\nfrom django_percentagefield.db.models import PercentageField\n\n\nclass YourModel(models.Model):\n    percentage_field = PercentageField()\n```\n\n- in your ``admin.py``, add the following wherever you use ``PercentageField``:\n\n```python admin.py\nfrom django.contrib import admin\nfrom django.utils.translation import gettext_lazy as _\nfrom django_percentagefield.utils import format_percentage\n\nfrom .models import YourModel\n\n\n@admin.register(YourModel)\nclass YourModelAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):\n    list_display = ('formatted_percentage_field',)\n\n    def formatted_percentage_field(self, instance: YourModel) -> str:\n        return format_percentage(value=instance.percentage_field, include_percentage_symbol=True)\n\n    formatted_percentage_field.short_description = _('PercentageField description')\n```\n\n- _[optional]_: add ``PERCENTAGE_MAX_DIGITS`` and ``PERCENTAGE_DECIMAL_PLACES`` to your ``settings.py`` (default values\n  ``7`` and ``4`` respectively)\n\n**TODO**: make the ``django-percentagefield`` package handle the formatting in ``list_display``, ``readonly_fields``,\netc. automatically.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "django_percentagefield.utils.is_unfold_admin_decimal_field_widget", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "any", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.utils.format_percentage", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": {"name": "Decimal | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "include_percentage_symbol", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.utils.format_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message", "type": {"name": "any", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "models.Model", "xref": {"fqname": "django.db.models.Model", "project": "django"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "SafeString | Any", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.apps", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "django_percentagefield.apps.PercentageFieldConfig", "bases": ["AppConfig"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "django_percentagefield.apps.PercentageFieldConfig.default_auto_field", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.apps.PercentageFieldConfig.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.db.models", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "django_percentagefield.db.models.fields_all", "xref": {"fqname": "django_percentagefield.db.models.fields.__all__", "project": null}}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.db.models.PercentageField", "xref": {"fqname": "django_percentagefield.db.models.fields.PercentageField", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.db.models.fields", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "django_percentagefield.db.models.fields.PercentageField", "xref": {"fqname": "django_percentagefield.db.models.fields.percentage_field.PercentageField", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.db", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_percentagefield.forms", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variab